### ✅ **Summary**

This projector function allows you to maintain a consistent and up-to-date `CartSummary` read model by applying `ShoppingCartEvent`s. It is robust, extensible, and can be adapted to support additional event types as needed.

When reconstructing the state of an aggregate in an event-sourced system, two primary strategies are available: **snapshotting** and **replaying the full event stream**. Each approach has its own set of tradeoffs:

---

### ✅ **Tradeoffs Between Snapshotting and Full Event Stream Replay**

| **Aspect** | **Snapshotting** | **Full Event Stream Replay** |
|------------|------------------|------------------------------|
| **Performance** | ✅ Faster load times (only replay events after the last snapshot) | ⚠️ Slower (replays all events from the beginning) |
| **Storage** | ⚠️ Increased storage overhead (snapshots take up space) | ✅ No additional storage overhead |
| **Consistency** | ⚠️ Risk of inconsistency if snapshots are corrupted or out of sync | ✅ Always consistent (based on the full event history) |
| **Auditability** | ⚠️ May lose visibility into full history (unless combined with full replay) | ✅ Full historical visibility |
| **Complexity** | ⚠️ More complex to manage (e.g., snapshot versioning, retention policies) | ✅ Simpler to implement |
| **Recovery** | ✅ Faster recovery from failures | ⚠️ Slower recovery from failures |

